                <blockquote><q>** 导言

Ⅰ 纯粹知识和经验性知识的区别
The Distinction between Pure and Empirical Knowledge [41]

Ⅱ 我们具有某些先天知识，甚至普通知性也从来不缺少它们
We are in possession of certain Modes of a priori Knowledge, 
and even the Common Understanding is never without them [43]

Ⅲ 哲学需要一门科学来规定一切先天知识的可能性，原则和范围
Philosophy stands in need of a Science to determine 
the Possibility, the Principles, and the Extent of all a priori Knowledge [45]

Ⅳ 分析判断与综合判断的区别
The Distinction between Analytic and Synthetic Judgments [48]

Ⅴ 在理性的一切理论科学中都包含有先天综合判断作为原则
In all Theoretical Sciences of Reason Synthetic a priori Judgments are contained as Principles [52]

Ⅵ 纯粹理性的总课题
The General Problem of Pure Reason [55]

Ⅶ 在存粹理性批判名下的一门特殊科学的理念和划分
The Idea and Division of a Special Science, under the title &quot;Critique of Pure Reason&quot; [58]
</q></blockquote>
